context_meta.title: Kate Middleton's BAFTAs look had a subtle nod to feminism you may have missed
context_meta.summary: The Duchess of Cambridge may not have worn black to the British Academy Film Awards on Sunday (and she received some criticism for it) but she did give a nod to women that you may not have noticed. When Kate stepped out of the car and onto the red carpet, however, she was dressed in green. The British royals are discouraged from making any political statements (and in fact do not even vote), and many speculated that Kate would avoid wearing black to the event, even if she might personally believe in the movement.
